<subSubSection id="C33D2F9B991BFFA4FF79517B63B0EC7E" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B987C10991BFFA4FF79517B63B0EC7E" blockId="2.[151,1436,1186,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B953A002991BFFA4FF79517B6336EF17" bold="true" box="[199,315,1331,1355]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
Two males, genitalia slides number Noct-00275 (Gyirong, Tibet) (
<figureCitation id="131C6095991BFFA4FBF0517A66AFEF16" box="[1102,1186,1330,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1047,1070]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,291,1002]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,267,1023]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Adults. 1 – 3. Micardia pulcherrima. 1, male, holotype (BMNH); 2, male (Gyirong, Tibet); 3, male (Cona, Tibet). 4 – 5. M. pallens sp. nov. 4, male, holotype; 5, female, paratype. 6, M. distincta sp. nov., male, holotype. 7, M. minuta sp. nov., male, holotype. 8, M. munda, male, holotype (BMNH). 9, M. argentata, male, holotype (BMNH). Scales: 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
Figs. 
<number id="3DEF6E37991BFFA4FB2C517A66AFEF16" box="[1170,1186,1330,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="2.1">2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C6095991BFFA4FB0C517A66C2EF16" box="[1202,1231,1330,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Genitalia and sternite. 10 – 14. male genitalia. 10, Micardia pulcherrima (Noct- 00275); 11, M. pulcherrima (Noct- 00273); 12, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00271); 13, M. distincta sp. nov. (Noct- 00272); 14, M. minuta sp. nov. (Noct- 00274). 15 – 16. female genitalia. 15, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00277); 16, M. munda (Noct- 00276). 17 – 18. eighth abdominal sternite of female. 17, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00277); 18, M. munda (Noct- 00276). Scales: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">10</figureCitation>
) and Noct-00273 (Cona, Tibet) (
<figureCitation id="131C6095991BFFA4FE82511E6386EF32" box="[316,395,1366,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1047,1070]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,291,1002]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,267,1023]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Adults. 1 – 3. Micardia pulcherrima. 1, male, holotype (BMNH); 2, male (Gyirong, Tibet); 3, male (Cona, Tibet). 4 – 5. M. pallens sp. nov. 4, male, holotype; 5, female, paratype. 6, M. distincta sp. nov., male, holotype. 7, M. minuta sp. nov., male, holotype. 8, M. munda, male, holotype (BMNH). 9, M. argentata, male, holotype (BMNH). Scales: 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
Figs. 
<number id="3DEF6E37991BFFA4FEC2511E6386EF32" box="[380,395,1366,1390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="3.11">3</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C6095991BFFA4FE26511E63B8EF32" box="[408,437,1366,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Genitalia and sternite. 10 – 14. male genitalia. 10, Micardia pulcherrima (Noct- 00275); 11, M. pulcherrima (Noct- 00273); 12, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00271); 13, M. distincta sp. nov. (Noct- 00272); 14, M. minuta sp. nov. (Noct- 00274). 15 – 16. female genitalia. 15, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00277); 16, M. munda (Noct- 00276). 17 – 18. eighth abdominal sternite of female. 17, M. pallens sp. nov. (Noct- 00277); 18, M. munda (Noct- 00276). Scales: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">11</figureCitation>
), are examined. The specimen Noct-00273, in which the forewing is worn, looks slightly different from Noct-00275. In male genitalia, the right valva of Noct-00273 has the outer margin of apex slightly arc-shaped incurved, rather than smoothly straight in Noct-00275. We also compared both specimens to the 
<typeStatus id="549CC2B2991BFFA4FF29518A62F4EF86" box="[151,249,1474,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
photos of 
<taxonomicName id="4C270793991BFFA4FECA518B602BEF86" box="[372,550,1474,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="B953A002991BFFA4FECA518B602BEF86" box="[372,550,1474,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131C6095991BFFA4FD8B518A6075EF86" box="[565,632,1474,1498]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1047,1070]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,291,1002]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,267,1023]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Adults. 1 – 3. Micardia pulcherrima. 1, male, holotype (BMNH); 2, male (Gyirong, Tibet); 3, male (Cona, Tibet). 4 – 5. M. pallens sp. nov. 4, male, holotype; 5, female, paratype. 6, M. distincta sp. nov., male, holotype. 7, M. minuta sp. nov., male, holotype. 8, M. munda, male, holotype (BMNH). 9, M. argentata, male, holotype (BMNH). Scales: 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number id="3DEF6E37991BFFA4FDD5518A6075EF86" box="[619,632,1474,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). There is only slight variation among them. Both specimens are from adjacent locations to the 
<typeStatus id="549CC2B2991BFFA4FE1051AF63D3EFA3" box="[430,478,1511,1535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C270793991BFFA4FDDE51A06102EFA2" box="[608,783,1510,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="B953A002991BFFA4FDDE51A06102EFA2" box="[608,783,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Darjeeling, 
<collectingCountry id="F3303C80991BFFA4FC1B51AE61EEEFA2" box="[933,995,1510,1534]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">India</collectingCountry>
). Consequently, both specimens should belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C270793991BFFA4FEB9524363BBEC7E" box="[263,438,1546,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="B953A002991BFFA4FEB9524363BBEC7E" box="[263,438,1546,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
